<item>
            <title>[JDK-8301749] Tracking malloc pooled memory size</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8301749</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Memory not allocated via NMT and uncommitted memory contributes to a discrepancy between NMT and RSS.&lt;br/&gt;
It can be hard to distinguish between these cases.&lt;br/&gt;
If the VM can determine the amount of pooled memory by malloc it would help with both determining if a trim_native_memory is needed, or there are some allocations happening outside of NMT.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
It would be good if the VM can summarize the malloc pooled memory by using e.g. malloc_info(3).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
We can thus more precise account for RSS value.</description>
